1.3 Interactive: Solar Energy Output
Explore how the Sun‚Äôs luminosity changes over its lifetime:


Code
viewof sunAge = Inputs.range([0, 12], {
  value: 4.6,
  step: 0.1,
  label: "Sun's Age (billion years)"
})

// Calculate luminosity (simplified model)
luminosity = sunAge &lt; 10 ? (1 + 0.1 * sunAge) : (1 + sunAge - 10) ** 3

phase = sunAge &lt; 10 ? "Main Sequence" : sunAge &lt; 11 ? "Red Giant" : "White Dwarf"

























Code
html`
&lt;div class="interactive-container"&gt;
  &lt;h4&gt;Sun at ${sunAge.toFixed(1)} billion years old&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phase:&lt;/strong&gt; ${phase}&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Luminosity:&lt;/strong&gt; ${luminosity.toFixed(2)} √ó current brightness&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;div style="background: linear-gradient(to right, yellow, orange, red); 
              width: ${Math.min(luminosity * 50, 300)}px; 
              height: 30px; 
              border-radius: 15px;
              margin-top: 10px;"&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
`













Key Concept



The Sun converts 4 million tons of matter into energy every second through nuclear fusion. Despite this enormous rate, it has enough hydrogen to last billions more years!

14.3 Interactive: Moon Phase Simulator


Code
viewof dayOfCycle = Inputs.range([0, 29.5], {
  value: 0,
  step: 0.5,
  label: "Day of Lunar Cycle"
})

phase = dayOfCycle / 29.5
phaseName = phase &lt; 0.03 ? "New Moon" :
            phase &lt; 0.22 ? "Waxing Crescent" :
            phase &lt; 0.28 ? "First Quarter" :
            phase &lt; 0.47 ? "Waxing Gibbous" :
            phase &lt; 0.53 ? "Full Moon" :
            phase &lt; 0.72 ? "Waning Gibbous" :
            phase &lt; 0.78 ? "Third Quarter" :
            phase &lt; 0.97 ? "Waning Crescent" : "New Moon"

illumination = phase &lt; 0.5 ? phase * 2 * 100 : (1 - phase) * 2 * 100

moonrise = phase &lt; 0.5 ? 
           `${Math.floor(6 + phase * 24)}:${Math.floor((phase * 24 % 1) * 60).toString().padStart(2, '0')}` :
           `${Math.floor(18 + (phase - 0.5) * 24) % 24}:${Math.floor(((phase - 0.5) * 24 % 1) * 60).toString().padStart(2, '0')}`







































Code
html`
&lt;div class="interactive-container" style="text-align: center;"&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;${phaseName}&lt;/h3&gt;

  &lt;svg width="200" height="200" style="display: block; margin: 0 auto;"&gt;
    &lt;circle cx="100" cy="100" r="80" fill="#1a1a2e" stroke="gray" stroke-width="2"/&gt;
    ${phase === 0 ? '' : phase &lt; 0.5 ?
      `&lt;path d="M 100 20 A 80 80 0 0 1 100 180 A ${80 * Math.abs(1 - phase * 4)} 80 0 ${phase &gt; 0.25 ? 1 : 0} ${phase &gt; 0.25 ? 1 : 0} 100 20" fill="#f5f5dc"/&gt;` :
      `&lt;path d="M 100 20 A 80 80 0 0 0 100 180 A ${80 * Math.abs(1 - (phase - 0.5) * 4)} 80 0 ${phase &gt; 0.75 ? 0 : 1} ${phase &gt; 0.75 ? 0 : 1} 100 20" fill="#f5f5dc"/&gt;`
    }
  &lt;/svg&gt;

  &lt;table style="margin: 15px auto; text-align: left;"&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day of Cycle:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;${dayOfCycle.toFixed(1)} / 29.5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Illumination:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;${illumination.toFixed(0)}%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Approximate Moonrise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;${moonrise}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
`

15.4 Interactive: Ice-Albedo Feedback
The ice-albedo feedback is one of the most powerful climate feedbacks. As ice melts, darker ocean or land is exposed, which absorbs more heat.


Code
viewof iceExtent = Inputs.range([0, 100], {
  value: 70,
  step: 5,
  label: "Ice/Snow Cover (%)"
})

viewof solarInput = Inputs.range([200, 400], {
  value: 340,
  step: 10,
  label: "Solar Energy Input (W/m¬≤)"
})

// Albedo calculation
iceAlbedo = 0.85  // Ice reflects 85%
oceanAlbedo = 0.06  // Ocean reflects only 6%
avgAlbedo = (iceExtent/100 * iceAlbedo + (100-iceExtent)/100 * oceanAlbedo)

energyReflected = solarInput * avgAlbedo
energyAbsorbed = solarInput * (1 - avgAlbedo)

// Temperature effect (simplified)
baseTemp = -10
tempChange = (energyAbsorbed - 200) * 0.1
currentTemp = baseTemp + tempChange

meltRate = currentTemp &gt; 0 ? currentTemp * 2 : 0

















































































Code
html`
&lt;div class="interactive-container"&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Ice-Albedo Feedback Simulator&lt;/h3&gt;

  &lt;div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; margin: 15px 0;"&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: #e0f2fe; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;"&gt;${(avgAlbedo * 100).toFixed(0)}%&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;Average Albedo&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: #fef3c7; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;"&gt;${energyReflected.toFixed(0)}&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;Energy Reflected (W/m¬≤)&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: #fee2e2; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;"&gt;${energyAbsorbed.toFixed(0)}&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;Energy Absorbed (W/m¬≤)&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: ${currentTemp &gt; 0 ? '#fecaca' : '#bfdbfe'}; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;"&gt;${currentTemp.toFixed(1)}¬∞C&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;Surface Temperature&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;svg width="100%" height="120" style="display: block;"&gt;
    &lt;!-- Ice --&gt;
    &lt;rect x="0" y="60" width="${iceExtent}%" height="60" fill="white" stroke="#ccc"/&gt;
    &lt;text x="${iceExtent/2}%" y="95" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12"&gt;Ice (${iceExtent}%)&lt;/text&gt;

    &lt;!-- Ocean --&gt;
    &lt;rect x="${iceExtent}%" y="60" width="${100-iceExtent}%" height="60" fill="#1E90FF"/&gt;
    &lt;text x="${iceExtent + (100-iceExtent)/2}%" y="95" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="white"&gt;Ocean (${100-iceExtent}%)&lt;/text&gt;

    &lt;!-- Sun rays --&gt;
    &lt;line x1="50%" y1="0" x2="30%" y2="55" stroke="orange" stroke-width="3" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/&gt;
    &lt;line x1="50%" y1="0" x2="70%" y2="55" stroke="orange" stroke-width="3"/&gt;

    &lt;!-- Reflected rays --&gt;
    &lt;line x1="30%" y1="55" x2="15%" y2="10" stroke="yellow" stroke-width="${avgAlbedo * 3}" opacity="0.7"/&gt;
  &lt;/svg&gt;

  &lt;div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 15px;"&gt;
    &lt;strong&gt;Feedback Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt;
    ${currentTemp &gt; 0 ? 
      `&lt;p style="color: #dc2626;"&gt;‚ö†Ô∏è Temperature above freezing! Ice melting at ~${meltRate.toFixed(1)}% per year. 
       As ice melts ‚Üí albedo decreases ‚Üí more absorption ‚Üí more warming ‚Üí MORE MELTING (positive feedback loop!)&lt;/p&gt;` :
      `&lt;p style="color: #2563eb;"&gt;‚ùÑÔ∏è Temperature below freezing. Ice stable or growing. 
       High albedo reflects solar energy, keeping surface cool.&lt;/p&gt;`
    }
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
`

16.4 Interactive: Greenhouse Effect Model


Code
viewof co2Level = Inputs.range([280, 800], {
  value: 420,
  step: 10,
  label: "CO‚ÇÇ Concentration (ppm)"
})

viewof ch4Level = Inputs.range([700, 3000], {
  value: 1900,
  step: 50,
  label: "Methane (ppb)"
})

viewof albedoValue = Inputs.range([0.2, 0.4], {
  value: 0.30,
  step: 0.01,
  label: "Planetary Albedo"
})

// Calculate temperature (simplified radiative model)
solarConstant = 1361
absorbed = solarConstant/4 * (1 - albedoValue)
stefanBoltzmann = 5.67e-8

// Greenhouse factor (simplified)
ghFactor = 1 + 0.3 * Math.log(co2Level/280) + 0.1 * Math.log(ch4Level/700)

effectiveTemp = Math.pow(absorbed / stefanBoltzmann, 0.25) - 273.15
surfaceTemp = effectiveTemp + 33 * ghFactor

preindustrialTemp = 14
tempAnomaly = surfaceTemp - preindustrialTemp

















































































Code
html`
&lt;div class="interactive-container"&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;Greenhouse Effect Model&lt;/h3&gt;

  &lt;div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 15px; margin: 15px 0;"&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: #fef2f2; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; color: #dc2626;"&gt;${surfaceTemp.toFixed(1)}¬∞C&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;Global Mean Temperature&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: ${tempAnomaly &gt; 0 ? '#fef2f2' : '#f0fdf4'}; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; color: ${tempAnomaly &gt; 0 ? '#dc2626' : '#16a34a'};"&gt;
        ${tempAnomaly &gt; 0 ? '+' : ''}${tempAnomaly.toFixed(2)}¬∞C
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;Anomaly from Pre-industrial&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style="background: #eff6ff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;"&gt;
      &lt;div style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; color: #2563eb;"&gt;${ghFactor.toFixed(2)}&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;Greenhouse Factor&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px;"&gt;
    &lt;strong&gt;Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt;
    &lt;ul style="margin: 10px 0;"&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Pre-industrial CO‚ÇÇ: 280 ppm ‚Üí Current: ${co2Level} ppm (${((co2Level/280 - 1) * 100).toFixed(0)}% increase)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Without greenhouse effect, Earth would be ${(-effectiveTemp).toFixed(0)}¬∞C (frozen!)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;${tempAnomaly &gt; 1.5 ? "‚ö†Ô∏è Exceeds Paris Agreement 1.5¬∞C target!" : 
           tempAnomaly &gt; 1 ? "‚ö†Ô∏è Approaching dangerous warming levels" :
           "Within relatively safe warming range"}&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
`
